# Home Page ↔ Section Page Sync

Every content section exists in **two places** that must always stay identical:

| Section   | Dedicated page                                      | Home page embed (HomeClient.tsx)         |
|-----------|-----------------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------|
| Education | `src/app/[locale]/about/page.tsx`                   | `#education` block in `HomeClient.tsx`   |
| Experience| `src/app/[locale]/experience/page.tsx`              | `#experience` block in `HomeClient.tsx`  |
| Projects  | `src/app/[locale]/projects/page.tsx`                | `#projects` block in `HomeClient.tsx`    |
| Skills    | `src/app/[locale]/skills/page.tsx`                  | `#skills` block in `HomeClient.tsx`      |
| Awards    | `src/app/[locale]/awards/page.tsx`                  | `#awards` block in `HomeClient.tsx`      |
| Contact   | `src/app/[locale]/contact/ContactPageContent.tsx`   | `#contact` block in `HomeClient.tsx`     |

## Rule

Whenever a change is made to **either** location, **always** apply the equivalent change to the other location in the same edit session — layout, styling, component structure, content, and data must remain in sync.

- Changing a card layout on the Skills page → update the `#skills` block in `HomeClient.tsx` too.
- Changing a filter tab on the Projects home block → update `projects/page.tsx` too.
- Content lives in `messages/en.json` and `messages/fr.json` — one edit there covers both automatically.
